<h1>Yogurt Pancakes</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>3/4 cup plain whole-milk Greek yogurt  </li>
<li>3/4 cup milk  </li>
<li>2 eggs  </li>
<li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil  </li>
<li>1 cup all-purpose flour  </li>
<li>1 tablespoon maple syrup  </li>
<li>2 teaspoons baking powder  </li>
<li>¼ teaspoon salt</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
<li>In a medium bowl, whisk together the yogurt, milk, eggs, vegetable oil, and maple syrup until smooth.  </li>
<li>Add the flour, baking powder, and salt. Whisk gently until just combined.  </li>
<li>Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Lightly grease with oil or nonstick spray.  </li>
<li>Spoon about 1/4 cup batter per pancake (or 2 tablespoons for mini pancakes). Cook for 3–4 minutes, until bubbles form on the surface and the edges set.  </li>
<li>Flip and cook for another 3 minutes.  </li>
<li>Serve warm with applesauce, fruit puree, maple syrup, or nut/seed butter.  </li>
</ol>
